               <objectContents>
                  <ab type="description">Some 24 people are standing in front of the Yugoslav consulate, waiting for the doors to be opened. Most of these individuals are men, but at least two women are noticable as well. All are wearing clothes for the winter season. Two men are looking at the camera. Some people wear bags for documents. The door and the façade of the building are the background of the photo. Two plaques are noticable, with the title of the institution and the Yugoslav coat of arms. </ab>
                  <ab type="comment">The photographer is positioned almost centrally (slighlty diagonally) in front of the entrance of the consulate, and close to the people he is observing. Most probably he is standind in the middle of the small street or on the other sidewalk.</ab>
